				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Rhasin I was going to cover that, but sure you can add the other armour to the pet, if you have time or inclination to do it. The odds are if the pet scales, you won't need to. Though if going into a tough situation you may max it out. 
<br />

<br />
Nothing wrong with that. The odds are though the item summoned onto the pet should be good enough to not need the other items. Or if so, just have it fill all slots when you click the item. So you can't add more to the pet, but 2 weapons. Though making it not do so, has an advantage. You may just summon phantom plate for the pet just in case, as well as focus items for 120 more hit points. Sure flexability, if you want to spend the time/mana to max the pet, sure why not. The final numbers could take that into acount. The thing I am gettting at, is making a focus item replace muzzle, Belt, and and upping the pet a lot, so all you really need do is hand it 2 weapons for the content your facing. To lower the number of items we need to summon to fight, not increase it.
<br />

<br />
As for nodrop. The item is a targeted summoned belt from a right click item. So not no drop, but only will go onto your pet. So not an issue, as you can not make them to hold or give out. Like burnout, click it and your pet is the only one that will receive the item.
